      "highlights": [
        "INTERCONNECTION CUSTOMER SUBMIT AN INTERCONNECTION REQUEST?........................................1  ...    6. WHAT IS THE STUDY PROCESS FOR GENERATION INTERCONNECTION PROJECTS?........................................................2  ...    The purpose of this guide is to: • Provide interconnection customers with an introduction to and a high-level summary of various  ...    The purpose of the NYISO Transmission Expansion & Interconnection process is to: • Evaluate impacts of proposed generation, transmission and load projects on the New York State Transmission System and distribution system, as applicable • Identify and cost allocate upgrade facilities required to meet reliability requirements (i.e., System Upgrade Facilities or Network Upgrade Facilities) and, for projects requesting Capacity Resource  ...    • OATT Attachment HH – Standard Interconnection Procedures for Generating Facilities, Cluster  ...    IP Support team at Stakeholder_Services_IPsupport@nyiso.com 6. What is the study process for generation interconnection projects? The NYISO’s interconnection process include two processes that evaluate proposed interconnections of Generating Facilities (and Cluster Study Transmission Projects) and Load, respectively. Not all proposed interconnections fall under the NYISO’s interconnection procedures or under FERC’s  ...    ▪ Generating Facilities that intend to participate in the NYISO wholesale sales.  ...    directly connected to the Cluster Study Transmission Project \n▪ Material modifications to existing Facilities. o An Interconnection Request can be submitted via the online platform and requires: ▪ Non-refundable Application Fee of $10,000 (cash only) or $5,000 for CRIS-Only \nprojects ▪ Study Deposit (cash, letter of credit or surety bond)\n$50,000 for a CRIS-Only Request ▪ Conceptual one-line diagram that includes:\n• The Project name, and the Interconnection Customer name on the diagram; • The facility address (specific location – coordinates or closest street address);  ...    ▪ Demonstration of Site Control2\n▪ Interconnection Customers are required to pay the actual study costs under the requirements of the NYISO’s SIP in Attachment HH to the NYISO OATT and ISO  ...    the Cluster Study Agreement for the Interconnection Request or the CRIS-Only \nRequest. o The basic steps of the SIP are:\n▪ Pre-Application Process (optional)  ...    Transmission Expansion and Interconnection User’s Guide | 5 o A TIP Interconnection Request can be submitted via the online platform and requires a $10,000 non-refundable application fee and study data\no The TIP includes three interconnection study phases: ▪ Optional Feasibility Study (OFES) - $60,000 study deposit \n▪ System Impact Study (SIS) - $120,000 study deposit ▪ Facilities Study - $100,000 study deposit \no Transmission Developers are required to pay the actual study costs. o The basic steps of the TIP are:\n▪ Initial Processing of the TIP Application\n▪ Scoping Meeting  ...    • The Cluster Study performs a detailed study of the collective reliability impact of a group of  ...    o Final Decision Period: iterative decision rounds ▪ Interconnection Customers must elect whether"
